<doc id="981793" wikidata="Q867141" url="?curid=981793" title="Ehresmann's lemma">
<text>In mathematics, or specifically, in differential topology, Ehresmann&#x27;s lemma or Ehresmann&#x27;s fibration theorem states that if a smooth mapping formula_1, where formula_2 and formula_3 are smooth manifolds, is
# a surjective submersion, and
# a proper map (in particular, this condition is always satisfied if &quot;M&quot; is compact),

then it is a locally trivial fibration. This is a foundational result in differential topology due to Charles Ehresmann, and has many variants.

== See also ==
*Thom&#x27;s first isotopy lemma

